criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18 y.o. ≤age≤75 y.o.;

          -  Diagnosis of esophageal gastric varices by gastroscopy;

          -  Cirrhotic gastroesophageal variceal bleeding underwent endoscopic injection of tissue
             adhesive;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age <18 y.o. or age > 75 y.o.;

          -  Never had the variceal bleeding episode before;

          -  Do not have endoscopic injection of tissue adhesive;

          -  The cefotiam contraindications: such as allergies, pregnancy etc;

          -  combined with other malignant tumor (not exclude patients with hepatocellular
             carcinoma who don't not need treatment at the moment);

          -  Known infection before endoscopic treatment (Fever, microbial cultures positive, et
             al.);

          -  Massive ascites or combined with other high risk factor that require prophylaxis use
             of antibiotics;

          -  Acute variceal bleeding within 5 days;

          -  Refuse to participate
